# NOTE: the image is built from the REPO ROOT with `-f apps/web/Dockerfile`.
# Docker/BuildKit resolves the ignore file as <dockerfile-path>.dockerignore
# first, falling back to <context>/.dockerignore. Because this file lives at
# apps/web/.dockerignore (not the context root), BuildKit picks it up via the
# `apps/web/Dockerfile.dockerignore` convention only if symlinked; to be safe
# the Dockerfile copies an explicit, minimal set of files rather than the whole
# tree, so correctness never depends on this ignore. It still trims the build
# context to keep builds fast and prevent secrets from entering the daemon.
#
# Patterns are relative to the build context (repo root).

# Dependencies — reinstalled inside the image from the lockfile.
**/node_modules

# Build artifacts — rebuilt inside the image.
**/.next
**/dist
**/coverage
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local Prisma generated output — regenerated in the build stage.
**/.prisma

# VCS / CI
.git
.github

# Secrets / local env — never bake into the image.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Editor / OS cruft
**/.DS_Store
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# Tests / e2e output not needed at build time
**/test-results
**/playwright-report

# Docker
**/Dockerfile
**/.dockerignore

# Mobile app — irrelevant to the web image
apps/mobile
